Welcome to Villa Catarina.
A grand Tuscan-style estate spectacularly situated on 550+ acres in the heart of Litchfield County offers unparalleled privacy and security as well as magnificent tri-state views of MA, CT, and NY. node.text:
Welcome to "Stormfield" - the iconic mansion built in Redding for author Samuel Clemens, best known as Mark Twain, who lived there from 1908 until his death in 1910.
Upon surveying the countryside from his new home, Clemens exclaimed “How beautiful it all is. I did not think it could be as beautiful as this.” He stipulated the house should be built in the style of a Tuscan villa, after having enjoyed time in Italy, and derived the property's name from his short story "Captain Stormfield's Visit to Heaven." After a fire in 1923, the current estate was re-built in 1925 on the same foundation, retaining the original terraces, stone walls, stone pillars, and formal gardens. The home is sited on 28.53 private acres and adjoins 161 acres of Redding Land Trust. Feel like you've stepped back in time where exquisitely appointed period details artfully blend with today's modern amenities. As one of Redding's signature properties and a rare opportunity to own a piece of American History, this home is not to be missed.
30 Mark Twain Lane, Redding, CT $4,200,000
4 Bedrooms
5/1 Baths
Don't miss out on the opportunity to own this historic home, listed with @LauraFreedAnconaHomes. Learn more via the link in bio.
